3. SR_4 : Hydraulic Actuator Control Loop Performance...

Link to Requirement Set
Document: HelicopterSystemRequirements.slreqx
Location/Item: SR_4

Hydraulic Actuator Control Loop Performance

The flight control system shall control the hydraulic actuator position with a minimum bandwidth of 10Hz and a minimum damping of 0.4. The steady state error tracking shall be within 5% of the position command.

4. SR_5 : Attitude Heading Reference System Interfa...

Link to Requirement Set
Document: HelicopterSystemRequirements.slreqx
Location/Item: SR_5

Attitude Heading Reference System Interfaces

The flight control system shall process three MIL1553 digital bus inputs from Attitude/Heading Reference Systems (AHRS), including pitch attitude, roll attitude, pitch rate, roll rate and yaw rate.

5. SR_6 : Attitude Rate Tracking Performance (Helico...

Link to Requirement Set
Document: HelicopterSystemRequirements.slreqx
Location/Item: SR_6

Attitude Rate Tracking Performance

The control system shall track set point changes in theta and phi within 1 degree steady-state error, rise time of 2 seconds (+/-0.5), maximum of 10% overshoot. The control system shall track set point changes in r within 0.5 degree/sec steady-state error, rise time of 2 seconds (+/-0.5), maximum of 10% overshoot.

6. SR_7 : Control Bandwidth (HelicopterSystemRequire...

Link to Requirement Set
Document: HelicopterSystemRequirements.slreqx
Location/Item: SR_7

Control Bandwidth

The control bandwidth shall be limited to 40 rad/sec in order to guard against high-frequency rotor dynamics and measurement noise.

7. SR_8 : Control Gain and Phase Margins (HelicopterS...

Link to Requirement Set
Document: HelicopterSystemRequirements.slreqx
Location/Item: SR_8

Control Gain and Phase Margins

The gain margin shall be a minimum of 10db and the phase margin shall be a minimum of 45 degrees in all axes.

8. SR_9 : Attitude Rate Authority Limiting (Helicopte...

Link to Requirement Set
Document: HelicopterSystemRequirements.slreqx
Location/Item: SR_9

Attitude Rate Authority Limiting

The flight control system shall limit the pitch and roll attitudes to 30 degrees, +/-10%. The yaw rate shall be limited to 15 degrees/sec +/- 10%.

9. SR_10 : Sensor Validation (HelicopterSystemRequir...

Link to Requirement Set
Document: HelicopterSystemRequirements.slreqx
Location/Item: SR_10

Sensor Validation

The flight control system shall determine the validity of each of the three AHRS prior to using the data from them.

10. SR_11 : Sensor Voting (HelicopterSystemRequirement...

Link to Requirement Set
Document: HelicopterSystemRequirements.slreqx
Location/Item: SR_11

Sensor Voting

When all three AHRS sensors are indicating valid, the flight control system shall use the middle value for each of the individual parameters.
When only two AHRS sensors are indicating valid, the flight control system shall use the average of the individual parameter values from the two valid AHRS.
When only one AHRS is indicating valid, the flight control system shall use the individual parameter values from that valid AHRS.

The flight control system shall process three LVDT inputs from the pilot cockpit controls, including fore/aft cyclic position, left/right cyclic position and pedal left/right position.
